cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with deep generative models for human body analysis, which is a problem related to computer vision (CV). The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning and semi-supervised learning, which are topics in machine learning (LG). The disentanglement of pose and appearance in the latent space is a technique used in artificial intelligence (AI). The datasets used in the experiments are related to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories, cs.GR and cs.MM, are less likely but still possible given the nature of the datasets used.
